RACE.RACE_TEXT: PENN NATIONAL RACE 1 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 43. Maiden Claiming Purse 17000. (PLUS UP TO 40% PABF) FOR MAIDENS, TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 121 lbs. Claiming Price $16,000, if for $14,000, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CALI HEAT dueled for the early lead three wide, made a two wide bid on the turn and drew clear by the quarter pole, then drew off leaving the turn and was ridden out to prove much the best. CHASIN' WHISKEY tracked the early pace towards the inside, made a two wide bid nearing the five sixteenths to be close up between rivals, could not keep up with the winner but ran on to be clearly second best. WARRIOR AT BAT tracked the early pace and made a three wide bid on the turn to press the winner but weakened, held show award. WORK FROM HOME was settled early on the inside, two wide advance two wide on the turn but lacked a late rally while just missing the show award. BIG SMILE hit the gate and stumbled breaking from the gate, then was four wide by the quarter pole and had no rally. DRAMA KEY was bumped and then bobbled after the start, saved ground into the lane and had no rally. POLIE dropped back. CHUCK ADAMS dueled for the lead on the inside and faltered.
